### 🧪 Registration & Authentication API Tests

### 1. Register New User
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Smith",
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "mobile": "9876543220",
  "password": "JanePass123",
  "role": "Student"
}

###

### 2. Check Email Availability (Before Registration)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/check-email/jane.smith@example.com

###

### 3. Check Mobile Availability (Before Registration)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/check-mobile/9876543220

###

### 4. Register Another User (Teacher)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Robert Johnson",
  "email": "robert.johnson@example.com",
  "mobile": "9876543223",
  "password": "RobertPass456",
  "role": "Teacher"
}

###

### 5. Login User (Legacy Endpoint)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "emailOrMobile": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "password": "JanePass123",
  "role": "Student"
}

###

### 6. Get Current User Profile (Protected)
@token = 
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer @token

###

### 7. Update User Profile
@token = 
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer @token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Smith Updated",
  "mobile": "9876543225"
}

###

### 8. Change Password
@token = 
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/change-password
Authorization: Bearer @token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "JanePass123",
  "newPassword": "JaneNewPass789"
}

###

### 9. Login with Admin Account (Test Credential)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "emailOrMobile": "admin@smartedu.com",
  "password": "admin123",
  "role": "Admin"
}

###

### 10. Get All Users (Admin Only)
@admin_token = 
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/users
Authorization: Bearer @admin_token

###

### 11. Get All Students (Admin - With Filter)
@admin_token = 
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/users?role=Student&status=active
Authorization: Bearer @admin_token

###

### 12. Get Specific User by ID
@admin_token = 
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/users/507f1f77bcf86cd799439011
Authorization: Bearer @admin_token

###

### 13. Update User as Admin
@admin_token = 
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/auth/users/507f1f77bcf86cd799439011
Authorization: Bearer @admin_token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Name",
  "role": "Teacher",
  "isActive": true
}

###

### 14. Deactivate User (Admin)
@admin_token = 
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/users/507f1f77bcf86cd799439011/deactivate
Authorization: Bearer @admin_token

###

### 15. Activate User (Admin)
@admin_token = 
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/users/507f1f77bcf86cd799439011/activate
Authorization: Bearer @admin_token

###

### 16. Delete User (Admin)
@admin_token = 
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/auth/users/507f1f77bcf86cd799439011
Authorization: Bearer @admin_token

###

### 17. Verify Token
POST http://localhost:5000/api/verify-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "your-jwt-token-here"
}

###

### 18. Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/api/health

###

### 19. Get Test Credentials (Dev Only)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/test-credentials

###

### 📝 INSTRUCTIONS FOR USE:
###
### 1. Install VS Code Extension: "REST Client" (humao.rest-client)
### 2. Open this file in VS Code
### 3. Click "Send Request" link above each request to test
### 4. Use @token, @admin_token variables to store token responses
### 5. Replace placeholder IDs with actual user IDs from responses
###
### For Postman:
### 1. Copy each request manually or
### 2. Import as Raw collection
### 3. Set variables for {{token}} and {{admin_token}}

